records.addlTxt:
Defendant Darren  Frank in court with attorney Jeffery Joy.  Defendant Darren  Frank in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Counsel have received the revocation packet and are prepared to proceed today.
Atty Hendee states joint recommendation for jail and sentence credit.  Believes the numbers would leave about 1 week left to serve.  Requests civil judgment if any fees are unpaid.  Atty Joy agrees with the recommendation.
BY THE COURT:
Court sentences defendant to serve 215 days in the Marquette County Jail, each count, concurrent, but consecutive to any other sentence he may be serving.
*Granted 155 days credit.
*Any unpaid fines/costs/restitution will be reduced to a civil judgment.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on September 10, 2018 at 11:30 am.
